  animalName: Moose
  icon: {fileID: 0}
  hints:
  - Ancient cave paintings in northern regions often depict this animal with large,
    branching antlers.
  - Remains show it was an important source of food and tools for early forest-dwelling
    peoples.
  - Fossil evidence links this animal to Ice Age fauna that roamed across cold northern
    landscapes.
  - Deep hoof impressions preserved in wetland sediments show a preference for marshy
    terrain, often far from dense human settlement.
  - Cave paintings depict a long-faced, towering animal with exaggerated head features,
    sometimes shown larger than nearby human figures.
  - Chewed bark layers on  trees reach unusually high above ground level, indicating
    feeding behavior beyond typical grazing height.
